group languages

group languages and order descending

next step would be to rename all variations of English to get total value

then to invesitgate within this English group as with other language groups

kaggle_goodreads_books %>% 
  filter(!is.na(language_code)) %>% 
  group_by(language_code) %>% 
  summarise(count = n()) %>% 
  arrange(desc(count)) %>% 
  #trying to change en-US to eng
  mutate(language_code, "en-US" = "eng")
`summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)

#group by author #Stephen King has most mentions

kaggle_goodreads_books %>% 
  filter(!is.na(authors)) %>% 
  group_by(authors) %>% 
  summarise(
    count = n()
  ) %>% 
  arrange(desc(count))
